RootCauseAnalysis - INFO -     Result: {'result': 'The log analysis reveals that all error logs during the fault window (2025-06-05T18:10:05Z to 2025-06-05T18:34:05Z) come from the **frontend** service, consistently reporting:\n\n> `"transport: Error while dialing dial tcp 10.233.46.196:7070: connect: connection refused"`\n\nThis indicates the frontend cannot reach a service at `10.233.46.196:7070`, which is likely the **cartservice** (standard port 7070).\n\nHowever, when attempting to search **cartservice** logs for the requested keywords (`OOMKilled`, `Error`, `exit`, etc.) using the UUID, the system returns **"Log directory not found for date 2025-06-05"**. This suggests **no logs exist for cartservice** during the fault window.\n\n### Critical Finding: Missing Logs\n- **frontend** has 30 distinct error log entries (with high occurrence counts, totaling thousands of errors)\n- **cartservice** has **zero logs** in the same 24-minute window\n\nThis is highly abnormal. A healthy cartservice should generate logs (even if just health checks or normal operations). The complete absence of logs strongly indicates the **cartservice pod crashed, was OOMKilled, or never started** during this period.\n\nAlthough the specific keyword search failed due to missing log data, the **lack of any cartservice logs** is itself critical evidence of a pod failure.\n\n```json\n{\n  "detected_log_keys": ["connection refused", "Error while dialing"],\n  "affected_components": ["cartservice"],\n  "missing_logs": ["cartservice"],\n  "log_summary": "Frontend services report \'connection refused\' to cartservice (10.233.46.196:7070). Cartservice has zero logs during the 24-minute fault window, indicating pod crash or termination.",\n  "next_verification": {\n    "action": "check_pod_lifecycle",\n    "reason": "Complete absence of cartservice logs suggests pod was not running during fault window",\n    "suggested_metrics": ["pod_processes", "container_restarts", "kube_pod_status_reason"],\n    "suggested_log_keywords": ["OOMKilled", "CrashLoopBackOff", "terminated"]\n  }\n}\n```'}
